SECTION 1 — DEFINITIONS

As used throughout this Agreement, the following terms shall carry the meanings
ascribed to them below:

1.1  "Software" means the entirety of source code, compiled binaries, object
     code, libraries, modules, plugins, scripts, configuration schemas, data
     models, trained machine learning parameters, prompt templates, API
     specifications, design assets, graphical user interface elements,
     documentation, test suites, and any other materials authored or curated
     by NuRichter Workspace and distributed under this Agreement, whether in
     printed, electronic, or any other form.

1.2  "Derivative Work" means any work that is based on, derived from, adapted
     from, or incorporates any portion of the Software, including but not limited
     to translations, adaptations, abridgments, condensations, expansions,
     arrangements, transformations, or other modifications in which the Software
     is recast, transformed, or adapted. A work consisting entirely of independent
     and separate works shall not constitute a Derivative Work.

1.3  "Contribution" means any original work of authorship submitted to NuRichter
     by any individual or legal entity for inclusion in the Software, including
     any modifications, annotations, additions, enhancements, or bug fixes,
     whether submitted via pull request, patch file, email, issue tracker, or
     any other communication means.

1.4  "Contributor" means any individual or legal entity that has submitted one
     or more Contributions accepted into the Software by NuRichter.

1.5  "Licensor" means NuRichter Workspace and its authorized legal successors
     and assigns.

1.6  "Licensee" or "You" means the individual or legal entity exercising
     permissions granted by this Agreement, and all employees, contractors,
     agents, and affiliates acting on their behalf.

1.7  "Commercial Use" means any use, reproduction, distribution, public display,
     public performance, or creation of Derivative Works intended primarily for
     or directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation.

1.8  "Non-Commercial Use" means use that is (i) personal and non-professional,
     (ii) academic research with no direct commercial application, or
     (iii) educational use by non-profit academic institutions.

1.9  "Distribution" means making the Software, or any Derivative Work thereof,
     available to any third party by any means, including but not limited to
     download, physical media, hosting, streaming, API access, cloud services,
     or embedding within another product.

1.10 "Effective Date" means the date on which the Licensee first obtains a copy
     of or access to the Software, whichever is earlier.

