SECTION 11 — COMPLIANCE WITH INDONESIAN LAW

11.1 This Agreement is designed to be compatible with and shall be interpreted
     in accordance with:

     (a) Undang-Undang Nomor 28 Tahun 2014 tentang Hak Cipta (Law No. 28 of
         2014 on Copyright);
     (b) Undang-Undang Nomor 13 Tahun 2016 tentang Paten (Law No. 13 of 2016
         on Patents);
     (c) Undang-Undang Nomor 20 Tahun 2016 tentang Merek dan Indikasi Geografis
         (Law No. 20 of 2016 on Trademarks and Geographical Indications);
     (d) Undang-Undang Nomor 11 Tahun 2008 jo. Undang-Undang Nomor 19 Tahun
         2016 tentang Informasi dan Transaksi Elektronik (ITE Law);
     (e) Any implementing regulations and ministerial decrees issued thereunder.

11.2 Where the provisions of this Agreement are inconsistent with mandatory
     provisions of Indonesian law, the mandatory provisions of Indonesian law
     shall prevail to the extent of the inconsistency, and the remaining
     provisions shall continue in full force and effect.

